Корреляция между отзывами и продажами¶

In [179]:
def relation_sum_score(platform):#        
    p = good_data_actual[good_data_actual['platform']==platform]
    print(p['user_score'].corr(good_data['sum_sales']).round(2))
    print(p['critic_score'].corr(good_data['sum_sales']).round(2))
    fig, (axis1,axis2) = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(15,6))
    p.plot(ax=axis1,kind='scatter', y='sum_sales', x='user_score', grid=True, alpha=0.6,\
           title = '     ')
    p.plot(ax=axis2,kind='scatter', y='sum_sales', x='critic_score', grid=True, alpha=0.6, \
           title = '     ')

#       
def sales_platform(r):
    sales_platform = good_data_actual.pivot_table(index='platform', values=r, aggfunc='sum')\
    .sort_values(by=r, ascending=False)
    top_platform = sales_platform.head()
    others = sales_platform[r].sum() - top_platform[r].sum()
    top_platform.loc['others'] = others
    return top_platform
In [190]:
#       
def sales_genre(r):
    sales_genre = good_data_actual.pivot_table(index='genre', values=r, aggfunc='median')\
    .sort_values(by=r, ascending=False)
    top_genre = sales_genre.head()
    others = sales_genre[r].sum() - top_genre[r].sum()
    top_genre.loc['others'] = others 
    top_genre = top_genre*100
    return top_genre
In [191]:
#       
def sales_rating(r):
    top_rating = good_data_actual.pivot_table(index='rating', values=r, aggfunc='mean').head()*100
    return top_rating
